item.title: Corning Museum of Glass Admission Tickets
item.description: See the world’s most complete collection of glass objects at the Corning Museum of Glass. Your admission ticket, valid for two consecutive days, grants you access to 50,000 pieces on display in about a dozen galleries. Witness an expert create a work of art at a glassblowing demo; marvel at the history of glassworks from Ancient Rome to Colonial America; peruse a variety of intriguing exhibits such as Glass in Nature and Paperweights.

image.alt: Corning Museum of Glass Admission Tickets

item.title: Canandaigua Wine Trail Experience
item.description: The Canandaigua Wine Trail— New York's original wine country—winds for nearly 30 miles across the Finger Lakes region, about 5 hours north of NYC. On this tour, you’ll get to sit back, relax, and enjoy tastings at four distinct vineyards, some “microfacilities” concentrating on small-batch, exclusive vintages. With rollings hills and waterfront vistas, the views always pair well with each sip.

image.alt: Canandaigua Wine Trail Experience

item.title: Glenn H Curtiss Museum Admission Ticket
item.description: Secure advance tickets to the Glenn H. Curtiss Museum to enter a world of vintage cars, historic aircraft, and classic boats, motorcycles, and bicycles. Booking Glenn H. Curtiss Museum tickets online combines the convenience of advance planning with the flexibility to arrive at any time of day, and you won’t be limited to a fixed tour schedule.

image.alt: Glenn H Curtiss Museum Admission Ticket

item.title: Canandaigua Lake Brewery Tour
item.description: Immerse yourself in the scenery of the Finger Lakes—and discover four of the region’s top craft breweries—on this small-group, half-day tasting tour. Following pickup directly at your Canandaigua Lake area hotel, hop aboard your comfortable vehicle and set off. At each of the four breweries, you’ll enjoy a tutored tasting, can try a range of styles, and can learn more about the brewing process. Upgrade to add a pub lunch to your itinerary.

image.alt: Canandaigua Lake Brewery Tour

item.title: Shared Wine, Chocolate and Cheese Tasting in Conesus Lake
item.description: Located on Conesus Lake, visit us and sample our four best-selling wines paired with cheese and chocolate. The sampling includes four gold medal awarded wines, Conesus White, Runway Red, Pebble Beach Blush and Max Black. Conesus White and Runway Red will each be paired with cheese while Pebble Beach Blush and Max Black will each be paired with chocolate. This will be a seated tasting and will also include a description of the wines.

image.alt: Shared Wine, Chocolate and Cheese Tasting in Conesus Lake

item.title: Zipline Canopy Activity Admission at Bristol Mountain
item.description: Are you ready to fly? Soar through the trees on our Zipline Canopy Activity. The Zipline Canopy Activity is an exhilarating experience that takes you on a journey through the treetops. With stunning views of the Bristol Hills, you’ll zip through the air on seven different ziplines. Your experienced guides will ensure that you have a safe and enjoyable experience as you take on this thrilling adventure.

image.alt: Zipline Canopy Activity Admission at Bristol Mountain

item.description: Looking to try something new and fun? We’re excited to introduce you to the sport of axe throwing! This thrilling traditional Canadian backyard pastime is now bigger than ever in urban communities. With the help of our talented axe throwing coaches, guests are able to share our passion for nailing the bullseye. No experience necessary, all skill levels are welcome!

item.description: Test your skills at Bristol Mountain Aerial Adventures. The Aerial Adventure Park offers over 120 elements, including zip lines, bridges, and ropes courses. Our experienced guides will provide you with all the necessary equipment and ensure that you have a safe and enjoyable experience. It’s the perfect opportunity to bond with friends, family, or coworkers while having a blast.

item.title: Wake Surfing on a Luxury Captained Cruise in Canandaigua
item.description:
There is nothing like celebrating a summer day with friends and family. Our captains will be sure to help you capture that perfect moment. We offer private and group captained cruises to help people get out onto the beautiful waters of Canandaigua Lake to enjoy some water sports action.
We are a full service marina located on the City Pier in Canandaigua on the north end of the lake. Create some special memories on your next cruise or charter.
Our captains are fully licensed and trained in boat safety, first aid, area history, and customer service.
Our cruises take place on our luxury Ski Nautique boats. We limit our public cruises to 6 passengers to have ample space for participants.

image.alt: Wake Surfing on a Luxury Captained Cruise in Canandaigua
